      "content": "i mean, \"complex philosophical hurdle\" sounds a bit like a cop out phrased to be polite. if the law isn't based on the text and what it meant when it was written, then the judges are basically just unelected legislators. at what point do we admit that the \"living constitution\" approach is just an excuse to bypass the actual law and push a political agenda?",
