      "content": "The tension you describe is precisely the core of American constitutional theory. When judges interpret the Constitution to incorporate modern social understandings, they are engaging in judicial interpretation, which some see as constitutionally legitimate evolutions, and others see as legislative usurpation. The debate hinges on whether the Constitution is a fixed document or a dynamic framework meant to govern evolving society. Admitting the \"living constitution\" approach is inherently political is a conclusion many originalists would reach, suggesting the system is flawed in its design.",
